      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Aim for a \"tightly curved\" spine—think of it as a gentle arch that stays straight but not stiff, like a board that’s been lightly bent to hold a weight. During the pull, your spine should stay in a neutral, slightly extended position while your ribs stay tight, and your abs should feel like a solid core cylinder. To brace properly, take a deep breath into your belly, then exhale just enough to keep your core firm without holding your breath. Imagine you’re about to get hit by a giant goblin; that sudden urge to brace will help you lock in the right tension.",
